Deputy President David Mabuza. GCIS JOHANNESBURG - A life of blackouts continues, even after Eskom's strike has ended. The power utility is implementing Stage 3 power cuts from 7am on Sunday morning. READ: Eskom to implement Stage 4 blackouts on Sunday afternoon It goes up to Stage 4 at 4pm on Sunday afternoon. Parliament now wants the Deputy President to update the nation on interventions to deal with the crisis. READ: SA’s electricity crisis | NPC calls for energy emergency Speaker Nosiviwe Mapisa-Nqakula has penned a letter to David Mabuza. She raises concern that blackouts are imposing untold hardships on citizens and businesses. Opposition parties are also calling for an urgent debate.